hell himself in the morning.

34
00:02:52,052 --> 00:02:53,954
You bastard! You've got him
a pass to Nanjing?

35
00:02:53,989 --> 00:02:54,920
Barnes!

36
00:02:54,955 --> 00:02:56,456
How long have we known each other,
you arsehole? Ten years?

37
00:02:56,491 --> 00:02:57,724
Will you excuse us, Mr. Appsley?

38
00:02:57,759 --> 00:02:58,884
Come on, Barnes..

39
00:02:59,092 --> 00:03:00,252
He's not press.

40
00:03:00,594 --> 00:03:02,010
Andy Fisher. Red Cross.

41
00:03:02,045 --> 00:03:03,427
That's why he got a pass.

42
00:03:16,009 --> 00:03:17,476
I made a deal with Andy Fisher.

43
00:03:18,378 --> 00:03:20,869
He gave me
his Red Cross papers and his truck.

44
00:03:21,615 --> 00:03:23,048
They'll get us into Nanjing.

45
00:03:23,316 --> 00:03:25,079
Barnes, we've got a scoop.

46
00:03:27,387 --> 00:03:28,649
I'm Andy Fisher.

47
00:03:29,456 --> 00:03:30,582
You're David Barcley.

48
00:03:31,725 --> 00:03:33,460
We're accredited drivers
for the Red Cross,

49
00:03:33,495 --> 00:03:35,485
bringing medical supplies to Nanjing.

50
00:03:36,897 --> 00:03:38,091
In this..

51
00:03:39,099 --> 00:03:41,067
Andy Fisher's in love, Barnes.

52
00:03:41,668 --> 00:03:43,067
He wants to get married.

53
00:03:43,570 --> 00:03:44,662
Now everybody's happy.

54
00:03:45,005 --> 00:03:46,267
Christ, you're nuts!

55
00:03:59,319 --> 00:04:00,520
Damn! Eddie!

56
00:04:00,555 --> 00:04:01,520
Eddie?

57
00:04:01,555 --> 00:04:02,721
Eddie Wei. He's in the back.

58
00:04:02,756 --> 00:04:04,291
You know. The photographer from U.P.

59
00:04:04,326 --> 00:04:05,543
I know who the hell he is.

60
00:04:05,578 --> 00:04:06,725
But what's he doing here?

61
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:08,523
He was desperate to come with us.

62
00:04:27,647 --> 00:04:29,547
Set your watch an hour ahead, Daisy.

63
00:04:30,050 --> 00:04:31,745
We're now on Tokyo time.

64
00:04:39,326 --> 00:04:40,987
