149
00:15:09,188 --> 00:15:11,213
Must've been the cold numbing the pain.

150
00:15:11,624 --> 00:15:14,855
Most of your blood's
gone down the Yangtze. But

151
00:15:15,394 --> 00:15:17,055
- I decided you'll live.

152
00:15:18,831 --> 00:15:21,061
I hope you're going to thank him
for saving your life.

153
00:15:21,968 --> 00:15:23,196
Thank you once again.

154
00:15:23,636 --> 00:15:26,002
She was talking to me. Right, Lee?

155
00:15:27,173 --> 00:15:30,506
So. You are in a hospital bed.

156
00:15:30,743 --> 00:15:32,768
- What?
- You talk a lot in your sleep.

157
00:15:33,746 --> 00:15:34,804
What about you?

158
00:15:35,381 --> 00:15:38,282
You didn't learn your English at Berlitz,
if I may say so.

159
00:15:38,918 --> 00:15:40,010
West Point.

160
00:15:40,519 --> 00:15:43,010
- I thought you were a Communist
- I am.

161
00:15:43,389 --> 00:15:44,788
Figure it out yourself.

162
00:15:45,124 --> 00:15:48,582
And when you do, you will understand
much more about China.

163
00:15:53,866 --> 00:15:56,391
I never thought of you
as the kind to pick up strays.

164
00:15:56,702 --> 00:15:58,226
Not male ones, anyhow.

165
00:15:59,205 --> 00:16:01,537
I can't just dump him out here, can I?

166
00:16:01,674 --> 00:16:04,006
Well he won't be up to
much for at least a month.

167
00:16:04,744 --> 00:16:06,405
I can't get him back to Shanghai.

168
00:16:07,446 --> 00:16:10,077
So, Miss Pearson.
Tell me what in God's name

169
00:16:10,112 --> 00:16:12,709
I'm going to do with
a six-foot Oxford graduate

170
00:16:12,818 --> 00:16:14,843
- who can't speak a word of Chinese.

171
00:16:23,629 --> 00:16:24,595
