You know I came back to
China to teach engineering.

174
00:16:32,538 --> 00:16:35,234
Now I'm teaching peasants
how to blow things up.

175
00:16:35,641 --> 00:16:37,700
To tell you the truth,
it's much more fun.

176
00:16:38,544 --> 00:16:39,511
Seriously.

177
00:16:40,279 --> 00:16:43,248
Seriously. I travel around to
organize the resistance,

178
00:16:43,449 --> 00:16:45,542
and try to stay ahead
of the Japanese army.

179
00:16:46,919 --> 00:16:48,187
I have to leave tomorrow.

180
00:16:48,222 --> 00:16:49,347
Take me with you.

181
00:16:51,490 --> 00:16:54,193
How fit do I need to be to
use a typewriter, for God's sake?

182
00:16:54,228 --> 00:16:55,751
I'm not worried about you.

183
00:16:56,329 --> 00:16:59,594
I'm worried about the poor bastards
who have to carry you around with them.

184
00:17:00,032 --> 00:17:02,262
But there is a place
up in the North-West.

185
00:17:02,335 --> 00:17:04,098
It's called Huang Shi.

186
00:17:04,370 --> 00:17:07,430
It's somewhere you can pick up
good background material

187
00:17:07,506 --> 00:17:10,100
and work on your Chinese
while you are convalescing,

188
00:17:10,209 --> 00:17:11,801
before you go on to the front.

189
00:17:18,517 --> 00:17:19,484
Very good.

190
00:17:19,552 --> 00:17:20,519
Did you understand it?

191
00:17:20,586 --> 00:17:23,419
I certainly did. You said -

192
00:17:23,756 --> 00:17:25,485
"Let me introduce myself."

193
00:17:25,624 --> 00:17:27,524
"I am a pumpkin."

194
00:17:30,329 --> 00:17:32,820
This area is controlled
by the Communists -

195
00:17:33,165 --> 00:17:36,191
this by our Nationalist brothers-in-arms.

196
00:17:36,702 --> 00:17:39,694
You will take the train
as far as Pao-Chi here,

197
00:17:40,106 --> 00:17:41,903
and Huang Shi's right about here.

198
00:17:42,007 --> 00:17:43,338
That's where you're going.

199
00:17:48,514 --> 00:17:50,243
- Chen?
- Hey! Get down!

200
00:17:54,186 --> 00:17:56,155
What's the matter?
They're not the Japanese.

201
00:17:56,190 --> 00:17:57,281
No. They are not.

202
00:17:57,390 --> 00:17:59,425
They're the government troops
of Chiang Kai-Sek.

203
00:17:59,460 --> 00:18:01,058
- Nationalists?
- Yeah.

204
00:18:01,093 --> 00:18:03,152
- I thought you were brothers.
- Sometimes.

205
00:18:03,229 --> 00:18:05,823
I thought you were fighting together
against the Japanese.

206
00:18:06,432 --> 00:18:08,866
When it suits them - or us.

207
00:18:09,702 --> 00:18:12,170
This could be one of those times. Or..

208
00:18:12,438 --> 00:18:13,700
maybe not.

209
00:18:17,410 --> 00:18:18,468
What are they doing here?

210
00:18:18,544 --> 00:18:20,711
They are conscripts.
From the south.

211
00:18:20,746 --> 00:18:22,548
They like to take them
far from their homes,

212
00:18:22,583 --> 00:18:24,641
so they are less likely to run away.

213
00:18:47,673 --> 00:18:49,197
They're trapped..

214
00:18:57,116 --> 00:18:58,674
Leave. Hurry!

215
00:20:49,295 --> 00:20:50,319
Hello?

216
00:20:53,332 --> 00:20:54,458
Hello?

217
00:21:03,208 --> 00:21:04,732
Who's in charge here?

218
00:21:15,421 --> 00:21:17,321
This is for the person in charge.

219
00:21:19,592 --> 00:21:20,889
I said,

220
